NAME
    Data::Format::Pretty::PHP - Pretty-print data structure as PHP code

VERSION
    version 0.03

SYNOPSIS
     use Data::Format::Pretty::PHP qw(format_pretty);
     print format_pretty($data);

    Some example output:

    *   format_pretty({a=>1, b=>2})

         array( "a" => 1, "b" => 2 )

DESCRIPTION
    This module uses Data::Dump::PHP to encode data as PHP code.

FUNCTIONS
  format_pretty($data, \%opts)
    Return formatted data structure. Currently there are no known formatting
    options.

SEE ALSO
    Data::Format::Pretty

    Data::Format::Pretty::PHPSerialized

